page.title: 10BIRDS
page.content: It is pleasing to note that nightingales have bred successfully this summer,a 50% increase on previous years.The montague Harrier has returned to a joining area,it's location a closely guarded secret.The most exciting species seen this year is the Wryneck.Although none have been observed on the site they have been observed locally throughout the spring and summer indicating that they have bred although as yet no nests have been located.At present man is able to expand in his variable pursuits and move about the forest without detriment to the bird life and there is no reason why he should not continue to do so provided the puplic is kept aware of the need to preserve our heritage.
